# Karpathy discipline (Chromatic Harness v2)

**Canonical policy:** [docs/governance/KARPATHY_DISCIPLINE.md](../docs/governance/KARPATHY_DISCIPLINE.md)

## Four pillars (mandatory for implementation)

1. **Think before coding** — assumptions explicit; ask if unclear; surface tradeoffs.
2. **Simplicity first** — minimum code; no speculative abstractions or config.
3. **Surgical changes** — read before write; scope to request; match conventions; no drive-by edits.
4. **Goal-driven execution** — verifiable done criteria before coding; run checks before claiming complete.

## Pre-implementation (state in chat before editing)

```text
Assumptions: [...]
Done when: [ ] check  [ ] check
Files in scope: [...]
```

